<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-06-15T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-06-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="240" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 Refugee Settlement Commission/64:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Special Mission at
                                    Lausanne</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lausanne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-06-15T18:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">June 15,
                                        1923—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 15—3:40
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>428. Department’s 182, June 13, 11 a.m. First meeting of Finance
                            Committee of the League of Nations will be held June 21st. I have
                            written a letter to the president of the committee in which I refer to
                            the suggestion made to the Department of State that Dolbeare is ready to
                            attend the meetings insofar as they relate to emergency relief.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>